Symptoms:
- Grafana dashboards show “No data”
- Logs not appearing in Loki
- Some VMs missing from Prometheus targets
- Gaps in metric timeline

Diagnosis:
# Check Prometheus targets (browser):
http://mntr.lab.local:9090/targets

# Check exporters running:
systemctl status node_exporter
systemctl status promtail

# Test exporter endpoints:
curl http://localhost:9100/metrics
curl http://localhost:9080/ready # Promtail

Common Causes:
- Exporter stopped/crashed
- Firewall blocking metrics port (especially Rocky Linux port 9100)
- Prometheus config missing target
- Promtail config incorrect
- Service restarted but exporter didn't

Solutions:

Restart exporters:
sudo systemctl restart node_exporter
sudo systemctl restart promtail

For Rocky Linux firewall:
sudo firewall-cmd –permanent –add-port=9100/tcp
sudo firewall-cmd –reload

Verify Prometheus config has target:
ssh jireland@mntr.lab.local
cat /opt/docker/prometheus.yml | grep [hostname]

Add missing target:
nano /opt/docker/prometheus.yml
# Add under scrape_configs:

    job_name: '[hostname]'

static_configs:

    targets: ['[ip]:9100']

labels:

            instance: '[hostname].lab.local'\\


docker compose restart prometheus

Check Promtail config:
cat /etc/promtail/promtail-config.yml
# Verify clients: url points to http://192.168.1.13:3100/loki/api/v1/push

Prevention:
- Enable exporters on boot (systemctl enable)
- Open firewall ports during exporter deployment
- Set up alerting for target down
- Document all monitoring endpoints
